plt.xticks(rotation=0, fontsize=12, ha='right')  # Adjust x-axis ticks fontsize, rotation, and alignment

plt.tight_layout()  # Adjust layout to prevent clipping of tick labels

plt.show()

    '3.00 - 3.49': 3.25,
    '3.50 - 3.99': 3.75,
    '2.50 - 2.99': 2.75,
    '2.00 - 2.49': 2.25,
    '1.50 - 1.99': 1.75,
    '1.00 - 1.49': 1.25,
    '0.50 - 0.99': 0.75,
    '0.00 - 0.49': 0.25
})

import pandas as pd

# Example metric names
metrics = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1 Score']

# Assuming mlp_results, xgb_results, nb_results, and rf_results are dictionaries containing the respective model results for each metric
# Initialize mlp_results, xgb_results, nb_results, and rf_results dictionaries if not already defined

# Example results for MLP, XGBoost, Naive Bayes, and Random Forest
mlp_results = {'Accuracy': 0.85, 'Precision': 0.82, 'Recall': 0.87, 'F1 Score': 0.84}
xgb_results = {'Accuracy': 0.82, 'Precision': 0.79, 'Recall': 0.85, 'F1 Score': 0.82}
nb_results = {'Accuracy': 0.75, 'Precision': 0.71, 'Recall': 0.78, 'F1 Score': 0.74}
rf_results = {'Accuracy': 0.88, 'Precision': 0.86, 'Recall': 0.89, 'F1 Score': 0.87}

# Create DataFrame
results_df = pd.DataFrame(data=[mlp_results, xgb_results, nb_results, rf_results], 
                          columns=metrics, 
                          index=['MLP', 'XGBoost', 'Naive Bayes', 'Random Forest'])

print(results_df)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))

for i, (model, matrix) in enumerate(conf_matrices.items(), 1):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i)
    sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g', annot_kws={"size": 18})  # Adjust fontsize for numbers inside the matrix
    plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix - {model}', fontsize=16)  # Adjust title fontsize
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Label', fontsize=14)  # Adjust x-axis label fontsize
    plt.ylabel('True Label', fontsize=14)  # Adjust y-axis label fontsize
    plt.xticks(fontsize=12)  # Adjust x-axis ticks fontsize
    plt.yticks(fontsize=12)  # Adjust y-axis ticks fontsize

plt.tight_layout()

nb_values = [accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_nb), precision_score(y_test, y_pred_nb, average='weighted'),
